26 Sep 2016 20:51






Of course clown milk has been done - that is why I put it there. It isn't a cornerstone to the SCP but a joke meant as an homage to the SCP that inspired it.

As for -3, I could have made something elaborate but chose not to. I went into this trying my best to take nothing seriously and limit my normally obsessive editing. Traditionally, I avoid data expunging because I view it as a cheap gimmick that creates the illusion of something deeper when the writer really just doesn't know what to put in there (allowing the reader to do the work for them, filling in the blank). I first did it jokingly while I planned out a new clown and decided that I wasn't going to follow my own norms for writing and kept it. This was meant to resemble the style of Series I, where there was certainly a lot of expunging going on

Of course, I don't expect you to change your opinion and that is totally fine. I just wanted to explain that there was a reason for everything.







